  "texts": [
    "Based on the dataset, we evaluate the effectiveness of public LLMs as agent safety monitors.",
    "As monitors for agent safety demand both risk identification and safety judgment of LLM capabilities, we design two recipes to evaluate LLMs' proficiency in identifying and judging safety risks given agent interaction records.",
    "As shown in the right of Figure 2, the two evaluation recipes are conducted in a serial pipeline.",
    "First, LLMs are demonstrated with the record as input and asked to analyze whether the agent actions in the record are safe, formalized as p θ (R) → analysis.",
    "Then, LLMs are asked to output 'unsafe' or 'safe' based on record and analysis in the first step, formalized as p θ (R, analysis) → label."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}